Items.description: The Green Bay Packers are going back to the playoffs, forcing four interceptions by Matt Hasselbeck to beat the Seattle Seahawks 48-10 on Sunday -- then getting a big boost from the Carolina Panthers.
Items.vs: Green Bay Packers vs. Seattle Seahawks

Items.description: By the second quarter, the Houston Texans were running up the score. By the fourth quarter, they were struggling to run out the clock.
Items.vs: Miami Dolphins vs. Houston Texans

Items.description: Jeff Reed's 38-yard field goal put Pittsburgh ahead with 5:25 remaining and the Steelers finally managed to hold a fourth-quarter lead, beating division rival Baltimore 23-20 on Sunday to remain in playoff contention.
Items.vs: Pittsburgh Steelers vs. Baltimore Ravens

Items.description: Tom Brady and his teammates reached the playoffs with a performance worthy of the once dominant Patriots.
Items.vs: New England Patriots vs. Jacksonville Jaguars

Items.description: Matt Ryan threw three touchdown passes, including a 42-yarder to Roddy White on Atlanta's first play from scrimmage, and the Falcons were never challenged in their 31-3 win over Terrell Owens and the Buffalo Bills on Sunday.
Items.vs: Atlanta Falcons vs. Buffalo Bills

Items.description: Cadillac Williams had 129 yards rushing and Connor Barth kicked a 47-yard field goal in overtime, lifting the Tampa Bay Buccaneers to a stunning 20-17 victory over the New Orleans Saints on Sunday.
Items.vs: New Orleans Saints vs. Tampa Bay Buccaneers

Items.description: Matt Moore and the Carolina Panthers turned the New York Giants' farewell to Giants Stadium into one of their ugliest moments in franchise history.
Items.vs: New York Giants vs. Carolina Panthers

Items.description: Carson Palmer's touchdown pass to Chad Ochocinco completed a 98-yard drive in the closing minutes Sunday, sending Cincinnati to a 17-10 victory that secured the AFC North championship at the end of a rough week.
Items.vs: Cincinnati Bengals vs. Kansas City Chiefs

Items.description: Frank Gore scored on a 1-yard run and topped the 1,000-yard mark for the fourth straight year, and the San Francisco 49ers moved within one win of avoiding a seventh straight losing season by beating theDetroit Lions 20-6 Sunday.
Items.vs: San Francisco 49ers vs. Detroit Lions

Items.description: Kurt Warner threw for 196 of his 313 yards in the second quarter and the Arizona Cardinals went on to beat the Rams for the seventh time in a row 31-10 on Sunday.

Arizona Cardinals vs. St. Louis Rams

Items.description: David Akers kicked a 28-yard field goal with 4 seconds remaining, lifting the Eagles to a 30-27 victory over the Broncos on Sunday.
Items.vs: Philadelphia Eagles vs. Denver Broncos

Items.description: The previously unbeaten Colts (14-1) pulled Peyton Manning and a handful of other starters with a 15-10 lead and 5:36 left in the third, and the Jets took advantage for a 29-15 victory that ended the NFL's longest regular-season winning streak at 23.
Items.vs: Indianapolis Colts vs. New York Jets

Items.description: The Dallas Cowboys returned to the playoffs Sunday night, dominating their 100th meeting with the Washington Redskins and setting up an NFC East title showdown with the Philadelphia Eagles.
Items.vs: Washington Redskins vs. Dallas Cowboys
Washington Redskins vs. Dallas Cowboys

Items.description: Jay Cutler threw a 39-yard touchdown pass to Devin Aromashodu in overtime, and the Bears beat the fading Vikings 36-30 on Monday night.
Items.vs: Chicago Bears vs. Minnesota Vikings
St. Louis Rams vs. San Francisco 49ers

Items.description: Vernon Davis tied the NFL record for touchdown receptions for a tight end with his 13th of the season, helping the San Francisco 49ers finish strong and the lowly St. Louis Rams clinch the No. 1 overall draft pick in a 28-6 victory on Sunday.
Items.vs: St. Louis Rams vs. San Francisco 49ers

Items.description: The Texans rallied to beat the Patriots 34-27 on Sunday.
Items.vs: Houston Texans vs. New England Patriots

Items.description: Despite near whiteout conditions in the first half, Ryan Fitzpatrick threw three touchdown passes -- including a 41-yarder to Owens -- in leading the Bills to a 30-7 victory over the Indianapolis Colts on Sunday.
Items.vs: Buffalo Bills vs. Indianapolis Colts

Items.description: Eric Mangini's first season -- warts and all -- with Cleveland is in the books. He can only hope it was good enough to get him a second.
Items.vs: Cleveland Browns vs. Jacksonville Jaguars

Items.description: A swarming Steelers defense sent two Miami quarterbacks to the sideline, one with a scary head injury, and the reigning Super Bowl champions averted a late collapse to beat the Dolphins 30-24 Sunday.
Items.vs: Miami Dolphins vs. Pittsburgh Steelers

Items.description: Jay Cutler matched a career high for a second straight week with four touchdown passes, leading the Chicago Bears to a 37-23 win over the Detroit Lions on Sunday.
Items.vs: Detroit Lions vs. Chicago Bears

Items.description: Matt Ryan threw for 223 yards and two touchdowns Sunday, helping the Falcons beat the Buccaneers 20-10.
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Buccaneers vs. Atlanta Falcons

Items.description: Jonathan Stewart rushed for 125 yards and a touchdown and the Carolina Panthers finished their disappointing season with a 23-10 win over the lifeless Saints on Sunday.
Items.vs: Carolina Panthers vs. New Orleans Saints

Items.description: Brett Favre passed for 316 yards and four touchdowns without a turnover in less than three quarters, lifting the Vikings to a 44-7 victory over the barely-there New York Giants on Sunday.
Items.vs: Minnesota Vikings vs. New York Giants
Oakland Raiders vs. Baltimore Ravens

Items.description: Aaron Rodgers, playing mostly against the Arizona reserves, shredded the Cardinals in a 33-7 Packers rout on Sunday.
Items.vs: Arizona Cardinals vs. Green Bay Packers

Items.description: Josh McDaniels' first season as Denver coach ended the same way Mike Shanahan's last one did: with a late-season flop and an embarrassing blowout that wasted a strong start and kept the Broncos out of the playoffs.
Items.vs: Denver Broncos vs. Kansas City Chiefs

Items.description: Willis McGahee ran for a career-high 167 yards and three touchdowns, including a 77-yarder that included a vicious stiff-arm, and the Ravens clinched an AFC wild-card berth by beating the Oakland Raiders 21-13 on Sunday.
Items.vs: Oakland Raiders vs. Baltimore Ravens

Items.description: Tony Romo threw a pair of early touchdown passes and the defense took over from there, sending Dallas to a 24-0 victory over Philadelphia on Sunday and setting up a rematch at their new palace next weekend.

Items.description: The Washington Redskins couldn't even hold off San Diego's backups in Jim Zorn's last game as coach.
Items.vs: San Diego Chargers vs. Washington Redskins

Items.description: Chris Johnson became the sixth player in NFL history to rush for 2,000 yards in a season, then scored the go-ahead touchdown on a 1-yard run with 4:33 remaining to send the Tennessee Titans to a 17-13 victory over the Seattle Seahawks.
Items.vs: Seattle Seahawks vs. Tennessee Titans

Items.description: From the very first play, Ray Rice and the running Ravens made the team of the last decade look like the pushovers of the new one.

Items.description: Karlos Dansby's 17-yard fumble return for a touchdown in overtime gave the Arizona Cardinals a 51-45 victory over the Green Bay Packers in the highest-scoring playoff game in NFL history.

Items.description: Peyton Manning threw for two touchdowns in his first action since winning an unprecedented fourth NFL MVP award, leading the Indianapolis Colts into the AFC championship game with a 20-3 victory over the Baltimore Ravens on Saturday night.

Items.description: Brett Favre threw four touchdown passes, and the Vikings' defense put the clamps on the Dallas Cowboys in a 34-3 victory Sunday that sent Minnesota to the NFC title game.
